column1: Supplementary Tabl 4.2. Phenotype data formatted for calculating correlations and QTL mapping.

Note: Only winter/extended cold temperature associated traits were used for QTL mapping in this chapter (columns D:AE). Additional columns used to calculate correlations. Planting replicates indicated as W1-W3. Spike replicates indicated as 1 or 2. anth = anthocyanin. OD = average of T and C experimental replicates. T = cold shock/LMA-treated. C = control/untreated.
